<div id="outline-container-sec-3" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="sec-3"><span class="section-number-2">3</span> Current themes</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-3">
<p>
Below is a sample of research themes I am currently working on. They are more
focused than the broad Research Interests sketched above, and of course change
a little bit as time goes by
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Episodes of Ozone increase caused by convective storms in the Amazon region.
</li>
<li>The applicability (and hopefully extension) of Monin-Obukhov Similarity
Theory (MOST) to the roughness sublayer over the Amazon forest.
</li>
<li>Surface Renewal Theory over water.
</li>
<li>CO<sub>2</sub> fluxes to and from Itaipu Lake, and more generally greenhouse gas
fluxes to and from lakes.
</li>
<li>The Hurst Phenomenon in Turbulence, and the existence, or not, of the
Integral Scale.
</li>
<li>Bénard-Rayleigh convection and similarity between temperature and a passive
scalar. 
</li>
<li>The nonlinear Boussinesq differential equation, its many incarnations, and
the search for new analytical solutions.
</li>
<li>Better estimates of wind velocity at 50 m from surface data and reanalysis
(I am currently looking at CSFR (<a href="http://cfs.ncep.noaa.gov/cfsr/">http://cfs.ncep.noaa.gov/cfsr/</a>)).
</li>
<li>Time-series analysis tools. Spectra and ogives.
</li>
<li>Air-quality (Ozone) diagnostics for the City of Curitiba
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-4" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="sec-4"><span class="section-number-2">4</span> Novos temas/New themes</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-4">
<p>
Eis aqui alguns desdobramentos dos meus temas atuais, e novos possíveis temas,
para alunos interessados em serem orientados por mim (em qualquer nível:
graduação (IC/TCC), mestrado, ou doutorado).
</p>

<p>
Here are a few sequels of the current themes, and possible new themes for
students interested in my supervision (at any level: Undergraduate Research or
Thesis, Master, or Doctoral research).
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Diagnósticos quantitativos da qualidade do ar em Curitiba, com base nas
séries de qualidade do ar disponíveis.
</li>
<li>Modelos de evaporação em lagos: Furnas e Itaipu.
</li>
<li>Soluções numéricias e/ou analíticas da Equação de Boussinesq para águas
subterrâneas. 
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


